# facts

- the project is a CLI for fact-driven development with coding agents
- facts works with a fact sheet, which is a flat list of validatable atomic facts

## format

### file
- the fact sheet is named .facts and lives in the project root
- the format is a valid subset of both YAML and Markdown

### syntax
- lines starting with # are section headings
- sections are semantically meaningful and group related facts
- heading depth maps to hierarchy
- each fact is a YAML sequence item (- prefixed)
- a fact can be a plain string or a mapping with label and command keys

### validation
- a fact with a command key is validated by running the command as a shell command
- exit 0 means the fact holds, non-0 means it fails

## cli

- the CLI is named facts
- written in Rust
- distributed as a single compact binary

## distribution

### npm
- published as an NPM package

### pypi
- published as a PyPI package

### install.sh
- install.sh downloads the binary from GitHub releases

## skill

- teaches coding agents how to install and use facts
- installable via skills.sh
- source is in ./skills/facts/
